</p><p class="- topic/p ">Whenever a customer gets into a dangerous situation operating the system the safety circuits make sure the customer does not get hurt in any way. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-EF6DDE4F-EB35-408E-97EF-B7EEFFD183A1" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The safety switches</title><table id="GUID-5B2FAFDA-6322-4717-9E30-6E1FF41D7B4C" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="80*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Component 
