</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-E9FB42E5-F9C0-4E33-8338-3ED7B66481E4" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Interlock (hardware and software)</title><p class="- topic/p ">The colorado system has implemented safety circuits in three areas to protect the customer against hazards .
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Process area:</b>
</p><p class="- topic/p ">All doors (topcover, manual maintenance, knife) which give access to this area are protected with safety switches. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Each door has two switches: one switch for embedded software to detect the status of the door and one switch (interlock) for disabling the power supplies. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">All three interlocking switches are connected in series and the status is send to embedded software (FRACOVEROPEN, +5V level when open, interlock active). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Software checks the consistency of all signals f.i. if one door switch is open the interlocking signal should also be active.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Software can enable the power supplies by signal FRA_COV_RL_N (activates relays on power distribution), but this will only work if all interlocking switches are closed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See highlighted signals in electrical diagram.
</p><fig id="GUID-4D7017FD-E781-40AC-8303-92DA1FECE000" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">Pocess area safety</title><image href="GUID-0BDFF56E-7D76-43AE-81F4-7C51171A9641-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0BDFF56E-7D76-43AE-81F4-7C51171A9641-svg.svg"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Media drawer:</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The motors of the media drawer are protected with two safety switches. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">One switch for embedded software to detect the status of the media drawer and one switch (interlock) for disabling the power supplies. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The status of the interlocking is send to embedded software (FRADRA1OPEN, +5V level when open, interlock active). Software checks the consistency of both signals. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Software can enable the power supplies by signal FRA_DRA1_RLN (activates relays on power distribution), but this will only work in the interlocking switch is closed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See highlighted signals in electrical diagram. 
</p><fig id="GUID-278E95EE-CCB9-4C0F-AD51-DAC163D30F39" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">Drawer safety</title><image href="GUID-BEC9860F-6F00-40ED-B36C-F023F348A1D4-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BEC9860F-6F00-40ED-B36C-F023F348A1D4-svg.svg"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Winder: 
</b>
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The motor of the external output winder is protected with three switches. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">One switch (19S1 WINDER DRIVE MANUAL) for embedded software to detect if the ouput winder is enabled and two switches (interlock) for disabling the power supplies. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The interlocking switches are closed when the winder core is correctly placed in the holders (left and right side). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The interlocking switches are connected in series together with the WINDER DRIVE MANUAL switch, the status is send to embedded software (FRAWNDOPEN. +5V level when open, interlock active). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Software checks the consistency of both signals only when the external winder is enabled. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See highlighted signals in electrical diagram. 
</p><fig id="GUID-C9AEE73F-23DE-4B69-8502-9FAB6F0FAA17" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">Winder safety</title><image href="GUID-6AD3AD92-DB9C-462A-A63C-3C993CCFB9AB-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6AD3AD92-DB9C-462A-A63C-3C993CCFB9AB-svg.svg"/></fig></li></ol></section><section id="SECTION_505547C4BC0F4F1B8B5A57A6892E53F5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Also see</title><ul id="UL_2B937589D07A4D968B51A1E088410D2B" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_792C31D4524A4E1BA753C86B0E67BF2A" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="22COMP01" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-F9B91945-CB0C-4E4A-AFEB-0B62B0D1872C.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 22 The components of Power?>22 The components of Power</xref> 
